  abstract = {S-bends with a widening of the width at the mid-bend and a Bezier curve transition are proposed and demonstrated for low-loss S-bends. The increased optical confinement and reduced transition loss enable low insertion loss (IL) and compact S-bends with longitudinal offsets as small as 2.5 $\mu$m and a wide operating bandwidth ($\sim$100nm) on a 220 nm thick silicon-on-insulator platform. The simulation results show ILs less than (0.22, 0.20, 0.20, 0.20) dB in the wavelength range of (1.5--1.6) $\mu$m, while the minimum ILs are (0.13, 0.13, 0.15, 0.16) dB for lateral offsets of (3, 6, 9, 12) $\mu$m. The experimental results show that ILs remain less than (0.41, 0.38, 0.36, 0.39) dB for the mid-bend widening Bezier (MWB) S-bends.},
